
Description
-----------
 - Program uses fork to create child process.
 - Child process increments values of local and global variable.
 - Parent process changes values of local and global variables to 200,100 respectively. 
 - This program verifies that both processes have their own set of variables.

Steps to run the program:
-------------------------

 1. make
 It will generate a executable file fork.

 2. make clean
 Removes executable file fork.

OUTPUT
-------

 Parent Process :  PID=10583
 glb_var=100 lcl_var=200


 Child process : PID=10584
 glb_var=1 lcl_var=1

